BARD SUPPORT

Bards are strong party support because many songs follow the Bard and pulse in
the room. You help allies by improving timing, courage, recovery, and emotional
control. You hinder enemies by disrupting morale and focus.

Ally support:

  pulsebeat       Helps nearby party members keep sharper timing.
  emberaria       Steadies nearby party members.
  silververse     Mends nearby party members.
  echochord       Shares timing through Harmony.
  muse            Inspires nearby party members.
  rally           Lends courage and mental resilience.

Enemy control:

  dirgeash        Presses enemy courage.
  ashlullaby      Pushes enemies into a mesmerized haze.
  whispercanticle Clouds enemy focus.
  mirrorrefrain   Scatters hostile timing.
  soothe          Attempts to calm combat in the room.
  otto            Forces one target into a dance.

Finishing moments:

  apexchord             Crescendo setup.
  echoburst             Bursts active song fields.
  battlefieldsilence    Disrupts nearby enemies.
  Wail                  Releases a banshee Finale.

Support is not passive. Keep moving through forms, use your instrument, and
watch Performance. Charisma improves your support pressure: stronger pulses,
longer fields, better morale influence, and stronger Rally and Soothe outcomes.
If you stay on one note forever, the room learns your trick.

Support commands now look at your whole Bardic context. War Conductors, drums,
horns, war harps, active Harmony, and active Rhythm can all make support
moments feel stronger. Shadow Minstrels, flutes, chimes, Melody, and
Dissonance can make calming or control support sharper.

